# Tables (`src/app/shared/table`)

**Advanced filtering:** see `table-filters.mdc` for filter defs, flyout accordion UX, chips, `buildFilterSummary()`, `optionTiles`, `StatusBadgeComponent` / `VehicleTypeDisplayComponent`, persistence, and per-page `*-table-filters.ts` wiring.

1. Row type in `*.model.ts`.
2. `export const X = defineTable<Row>()({ columns, filters, actions, endpoint, ... })`.
3. Page: `DataTableComponent` + `[loader]` + `tableCellKey(Table, 'column')` for custom cells. Optional `entityTab` (user hub tables) and `tableChromeVariant` (default `'splitCard'` — see `table-filters.mdc`).
4. **Page title row:** `PageTitleComponent` in the **page template** above `<app-data-table>`. See `page-title.mdc`. `DataTableComponent` does not render page titles.
5. **Create CTA (required on list pages with a create route):** `PageHeaderComponent` + `PrimaryActionLinkComponent` composed with `PageTitleComponent` — **not** inside `DataTableComponent` or `PageTitleComponent`. Parent page owns `createUrl` + `createLabelKey`. Reference: `portal/admin/features/vehicles/table/vehicle-table-page.component.*`. Skip CTA only when the list has no create flow (read-only).
6. Custom cell: `TableCellTemplateDirective` with `[appTableCell]="key"` in template.
7. **Route pair cell:** use `RouteDisplayComponent` (`app-route-display`) for origin → destination — not raw `{{ row.origin }} → {{ row.destination }}` in templates. Column uses `cell: 'custom'`; export key via `tableCellKey(Table, 'origin')` (or dedicated column key). Reference: `portal/user/features/transport/table/`, `portal/user/features/freight/table/`.
8. Mock data: feature `*.service.ts` with in-memory store from `*.mock-data.ts` until API exists — see `portal/admin/features/vehicles/data/`.
9. i18n: column `titleKey`, action `labelKey` in table def. Page header copy (`title` + `subtitle` + `pageIcon`) lives on the page component — not in `*.table.ts`.
10. Destructive row actions (e.g. delete): confirm via `ConfirmService` from `shared/confirm` before calling the API — see `confirm.mdc`. Add `…table.deleteConfirm.title` / `…message` keys per feature; use `shared.confirm.common.*` for button labels.

Do not rebuild pagination/filter/sort UI outside `DataTableComponent`. Do not use `window.confirm`.

## User portal hub tables (Plan 3)

Marketplace (`table-all/`) and our (`table-our/`) table page components are **not** standalone routes. Hub pages embed them:

- `features/find/find-page.component.*` — `TransportAllTablePageComponent`, etc. with `[embedded]="true"`
- `features/our-listings/our-listings-page.component.*` — `TransportOurTablePageComponent`, etc. with `[embedded]="true"`; hub header owns tab-specific create CTA

See `entity-tabs.mdc` for tab URL convention (`userFindUrl`, `userOurListingsUrl`, `userFindRoute`, `userOurListingsRoute`, `navLinkActiveOptions`).

**Entity service chrome:** pass `[entityTab]="'transport'|'freight'|'warehouse'"` on embedded `DataTableComponent` — controls-card accent, row hover; **mobile row cards have no entity left spine**. Default table chrome is **split card** (`tableChromeVariant` default `'splitCard'`). Styles: `_entity-service-accent.scss`, `_table-chrome-split-card.scss`. See `entity-service-colors.mdc`, `table-filters.mdc`.

## Table cell visual hierarchy (user portal lists)

When a table shows route/cargo/storage-style rows, reuse shared display widgets — **do not** invent per-feature badge/chip markup or use status colors on non-status data.

| Priority | Widget | Style | Use for |
|----------|--------|-------|---------|
| Primary identifier | `RouteDisplayComponent` | Neutral outline chips (`--chip-neutral-*`) | Origin → destination |
| Primary identifier | `WarehouseDisplayComponent` | Two-line primary/secondary text | Warehouse name + city |
| Workflow | `StatusBadgeComponent` | **Only colored semantic pill** in the row (`--status-*`) | Entity `status` — **not** service-type colors; see `entity-service-colors.mdc` |
| Period / deadline | `DateRangeDisplayComponent` | Compact inline text, tabular nums, `nowrap` | Merged from–to dates or single date |
| Secondary | `VehicleDisplayComponent` | Two-line primary/secondary text | Vehicle name + plate |
| Other | plain `format: 'text'` / `'number'` | Default table cell tokens | Description, size, weight, etc. |

**Merged date columns:** routes and storage expose one **Period** / **Availability** column (`…table.columns.period`) instead of separate start/end columns. Keep the column `key` on the **from/start** field (`transportStartDate`, `availableFrom`) so sort and `defaultSort` stay on start date. Use `width: '18rem'` minimum so ranges like `Sep 1, 2026 – Feb 28, 2027` stay on one line.

**Denormalized display fields:** persist table-friendly labels on the entity at create/update time (same pattern as routes):

| Entity | Form FK | Denormalized on entity | Resolved via |
|--------|---------|------------------------|--------------|
| Route | `vehicleId` | `vehicleName`, `vehiclePlate` | `CompanyVehicleService.getDisplay()` |
| Storage | `warehouseId` | `warehouseName`, `warehouseCity`, `warehouseLabel` | `CompanyWarehouseService.getDisplay()` + `getLabel()` |

Reference implementations: `portal/user/features/transport/table-our/`, `cargo/table-our/`, `storage/table-our/`.

## Mobile (≤768px)

- `DataTableComponent` renders a **card list** instead of the HTML table when the viewport is ≤768px (`MOBILE_MEDIA_QUERY` in `portal/shell/viewport.ts`, `isMobileLayout` signal).
- Table and cards are mutually exclusive (`@if` / `@else`); only one is in the DOM.
- Cards use column `titleKey` labels + values; custom `appTableCell` templates render in both views.
- **Entity row cards:** neutral border only — no entity-color left spine (see `entity-service-colors.mdc`).
- **Filter toolbar:** search + icon-only filter toggle same row; compact truncated chips — see `table-filters.mdc`.
- Optional column `mobile` metadata:
  - `mobile.primary: true` — card header (defaults to first visible column).
  - `mobile.hidden: true` — omit from card body only.
- Filters, pagination, selection, and row actions work the same on mobile.

## Route display custom cell

When a column shows origin → destination (neutral outline chips — **not** status colors):

```typescript
// *.table.ts — origin column, custom cell, often mobile.primary
{ key: 'origin', titleKey: '…columns.route', cell: 'custom', mobile: { primary: true } }

export const routeCellKey = tableCellKey(RouteTable, 'origin');
```

```html
<ng-template [appTableCell]="routeKey" let-row>
  <app-route-display [origin]="row.origin" [destination]="row.destination" />
</ng-template>
```

Page `imports`: `RouteDisplayComponent` from `shared/ui/route-display/route-display.component.ts`. Chip tokens: `--chip-neutral-bg`, `--chip-neutral-border`, `--chip-neutral-text` in `src/styles.scss`.

## Vehicle display custom cell

When a column shows vehicle name over plate number:

```typescript
// *.table.ts — vehicle column, custom cell
{ key: 'vehiclePlate', titleKey: '…columns.vehicle', cell: 'custom' }

export const vehicleCellKey = tableCellKey(RouteTable, 'vehiclePlate');
```

```html
<ng-template [appTableCell]="vehicleKey" let-row>
  <app-vehicle-display [name]="row.vehicleName" [plate]="row.vehiclePlate" />
</ng-template>
```

Page `imports`: `VehicleDisplayComponent` from `shared/ui/vehicle-display/vehicle-display.component.ts`.

## Status badge custom cell

When a column shows entity workflow status:

```typescript
// *.table.ts — second column after primary identifier
{ key: 'status', titleKey: '…columns.status', sortable: true, cell: 'custom', width: '9rem' }

export const statusCellKey = tableCellKey(EntityTable, 'status');
```

```html
<ng-template [appTableCell]="statusKey" let-row>
  <app-status-badge [status]="row.status" />
</ng-template>
```

Page `imports`: `StatusBadgeComponent` from `shared/ui/status-badge/status-badge.component.ts`.

All listable entities get a `status` field; each entity will define its own status union over time — see `entity-status.mdc`. Reference: `portal/user/features/transport/table/`, `cargo/table/`, `storage/table/`.

## Date range display custom cell

When a column shows a date period (or single date). **Do not** use two separate date columns when the UI reads as one range.

```typescript
// *.table.ts — keep sort key on start/from field; merge end/to into one column
{ key: 'transportStartDate', titleKey: '…columns.period', sortable: true, cell: 'custom', width: '18rem' }

export const periodCellKey = tableCellKey(RouteTable, 'transportStartDate');
```

i18n column keys: `portal.user.features.transport.table.columns.period`, `portal.user.features.warehouse.table.columns.period`. Form field keys (`transportStartDate`, `availableFrom`, etc.) stay separate under `…form.fields.*`.

```html
<!-- Range (routes, storage) -->
<ng-template [appTableCell]="periodKey" let-row>
  <app-date-range-display [from]="row.transportStartDate" [to]="row.transportEndDate" />
</ng-template>

<!-- Single date (cargo needed-by) -->
<ng-template [appTableCell]="neededByDateKey" let-row>
  <app-date-range-display [from]="row.neededByDate" />
</ng-template>
```

Page `imports`: `DateRangeDisplayComponent` from `shared/ui/date-range-display/date-range-display.component.ts`. Formatting via `formatDisplayDate()` in `shared/utils/format-display-date.ts`. Component uses `flex-wrap: nowrap` — widen column (`18rem`+) rather than letting ranges wrap.

## Warehouse display custom cell

When a column shows warehouse name over city (storage tables):

```typescript
{ key: 'warehouseLabel', titleKey: '…columns.warehouse', cell: 'custom', mobile: { primary: true } }

export const warehouseCellKey = tableCellKey(StorageTable, 'warehouseLabel');
```

```html
<ng-template [appTableCell]="warehouseKey" let-row>
  <app-warehouse-display [name]="row.warehouseName" [city]="row.warehouseCity" />
</ng-template>
```

Entity stores denormalized `warehouseName` / `warehouseCity` (like `vehicleName` / `vehiclePlate` on routes). Set on form submit via `CompanyWarehouseService.getDisplay()`; keep `warehouseLabel` for select labels and search. Page `imports`: `WarehouseDisplayComponent` from `shared/ui/warehouse-display/warehouse-display.component.ts`. Detail page summary band: `EntityDetailSummaryComponent` with `kind="warehouse"` — not in `*.detail.ts` — see `detail-page.mdc`.
